name: The seventh incarnation. Mosquito.
description:
I don't know how, but I was brought into the body of a mosquito. It's hard to imagine a conscious mosquito, right? It's good that life turned out to be short…

I hatched hungry. Very hungry. The only desire was to eat. Warm. Liquid. Many. Very much. 

The search for the victim did not last long, flying away from my swamp, I headed towards the hot glow. As I approached, a feeling of fear seized me. The closer I flew, the scarier it became. But hunger carried me to a warm sacrifice. After circling around a bit, I decided to sit on It anyway. 

Sat down. calmed down a little. Sucked. Thick, warm, the most delicious liquid in the world flowed into the abdomen. It was a moment of real happiness. 

Clap. And the soul went back to the mycelium - a favorite haven of disembodied creatures.

In the mosquito's spacesuit, I learned what Real hunger is. And also met a man again…
